property.name: text
property.value:
Colt is a "Open Source Libraries for High Performance Scientific and Technical Computing in Java." This model demonstrates a library of actors that generate random numbers according to various probability distributions.
The seeds and class of random number generator are coordinated among all instances of the actors in the model. Changing them for one actor will result in changing them for all actors so that the values are coherent. To change the seed or class of random number generator for all of the actors, right click on any one actor and modify the seed or sgeneratorClassParameter.
For a description of the allowable generatorClass parameter values, see the ColtRandomSource documentation.

property.name: text
property.value: Authors: David Bauer and Kostas Oikonomou from AT&T Research, and Edward A. Lee and Christopher Brooks

property.name: text
property.value: The Test actors verify that exactly the same random numbers are generated on each run (because the resetOnEachRun parameter of the generators is set to true). If the numbers differ from the expected on any run, then the test actors will throw an exception.
